	   <tr><td colspan=2>Very good post this one, short, informative and to the point. Not like some others here. One other thing to keep in mind is that there is sort of a haste cap =) Since only one item haste and one spell haste stack you can never get above that cumulative haste (note that I'm not saying anything about the delay here). Say Speed of the Shissar (think that's 66%) and a 50% belt. 100 divided by 216 (100 + 50 + 66) is approx 0.463. With the above example of a 30 delay weapon that makes a delay of 30*0.463=13.89 Haven't been able to ascertain if a bard haste stacks with this btw, but I guess that will come with lvls.<br><br>Shadowknight of the 49th season<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
